      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "[codex] Fix stale today usage buckets",
        "body": "## Summary\n- Use the current local calendar day for usage surfaces labeled Today instead of the newest historical bucket.\n- For OpenAI and Claude Admin API UTC daily buckets, include buckets whose `[startTime, endTime)` overlaps the local day so positive-timezone morning usage is not dropped.\n- Share day-bucket lookup helpers across local cost snapshots plus OpenAI and Claude Admin API snapshots.\n- Preserve explicit latest-bucket behavior for Bedrock and Mistral, and add regression coverage for stale histories and positive-timezone overlap.\n\n## Root Cause\nDaily usage history can be sparse or stale, but several UI paths labeled the newest available daily bucket as Today. That allowed yesterday or older usage to appear as current-day usage. For Admin API buckets, selecting by bucket label/start day also missed the UTC bucket that overlaps the start of the local day for users east of UTC.\n\n## Impact\nWhen no current-day usage bucket exists, Today now renders zero cost/tokens instead of stale values. For OpenAI and Claude Admin API history, Today now includes UTC daily buckets that overlap the user’s local day. The fix is lightweight: it selects from already-parsed history and does not add network calls or broad scanning.\n\n## Validation\n- `make test` passed all 43 shards.\n- `swift test --filter AdminAPIUsageLocalDaySelectionTests` passed.\n- `swift test --filter OpenAIAPIUsageFetcherTests && swift test --filter ClaudeAdminAPIUsageTests && swift test --filter OpenAIAPIMenuCardModelTests && swift test --filter ClaudeAdminAPIInlineDashboardModelTests` passed.\n- `swiftformat Sources Tests --lint` passed.\n- `swiftlint --strict` passed.\n- `git diff --check` passed.\n- `make check` was attempted but is blocked by a pre-existing upstream docs lint issue: `node --check docs/site.js` treats the file's ESM `import` as CommonJS.\n\nFixes #1705\n",
        "branch": "codex/fix-issue-1705",
